#### Is there anything else we should know?

Missing instruction on how to implement the following solution:

I have a material autocomplete field as follows:

`<mat-form-field class="example-full-width">
    <input matInput placeholder="State" aria-label="State" [matAutocomplete]="auto" [formControl]="stateCtrl" (keyup.Esc)="onEscape($event)">
    <mat-autocomplete #auto="matAutocomplete">
      <mat-option *ngFor="let state of filteredStates | async" [value]="state.name">
        <img class="example-option-img" aria-hidden [src]="state.flag" height="25">
        <span>{{state.name}}</span> |
        <small>Population: {{state.population}}</small>
      </mat-option>
    </mat-autocomplete>
  </mat-form-field>`

the onEscape is defined in the .ts file as follows:

onEscape(event): void {
 
// what to go here ???

}
What I would like to happen is if the suggestion panel is open and/or the user has selected an option, at that point I would like to allow the Escape key to programmatically return the auto complete to the state it would be in when the component loads and the mouse clicks on the input field.

There are several, what appear to be useful properties and methods, one that stands out is MatAutocompleteTrigger._handleKeydown
But no documentation anywhere on how to implement this.

I have a hunch, maybe I should try something like this:

ngAfterViewInit(){
  this.trigger.panelClosingActions.subscribe(options => {
      // but what to put here ? - I'm a noob with rxjs stuff :(
 });
}

There are jo examples anywhere on how to make use of MatAutocompleteTrigger.

Things I've already tried in the onEscape method:

1) this.stateCtrl.setValue(''); - this correctly blanks the field but doesn't cause the blur and re-focus behaviour that you normally get from clicking outside the control then back in it .
